      <h2>Operations Management with Receipts</h2>
      <p>Abraham Otieno is a Nairobi, Kenya-based operations manager and operations partner who builds reliability systems for BPOs, fintechs, startups, and founder-led companies, remotely, worldwide. The numbers behind that sentence: 80% faster team response times, 200+ agents onboarded, 100% project success rate across 10+ companies including Pioneer Outsourcing BPO, M-KOPA, OKash Kenya, and Generation Kenya.</p>

      <h2 style="margin-top: var(--space-7);">The Problem This Role Solves</h2>
      <p>Scaling teams don't fail because people stop trying. They fail because nothing is visible: commitments live in DMs, response times drift, onboarding is tribal knowledge, and leadership finds out about problems from angry customers. An operations manager replaces that with systems:</p>
      <ul style="color: var(--ink-muted); padding-left: var(--space-5);">
        <li><strong>SLA tracking:</strong> Response and resolution targets, measured weekly, owned by name. This is the discipline that produced the 80% response-time improvement.</li>
        <li><strong>Dashboards that leadership actually reads:</strong> CRM hygiene, KPI rollups, exception flags, replacing four spreadsheets and a Slack channel. <a href="/portfolio/">See a live example</a>.</li>
        <li><strong>Onboarding playbooks:</strong> Documented, repeatable, QA-checked. 200+ agents brought to performance this way.</li>
        <li><strong>Process documentation:</strong> SOPs that survive staff turnover and audits.</li>
        <li><strong>Weekly operating rhythm:</strong> The meeting cadence and reporting loop that keeps all of the above alive.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 style="margin-top: var(--space-7);">Kenya-Based, Globally Deployed</h2>
      <p>Operations management is remote-native work: the systems live in your CRM, your ticketing stack, your docs. From Nairobi (EAT, UTC+3) I run live overlap with Europe all day and the US East Coast through early afternoon, with async coverage beyond. For US and EU companies, the economics are direct: senior operations leadership at 50–70% below domestic rates, from a market where international-grade customer operations is the home industry. For the full argument, read <a href="/blog/why-nairobi-is-best-source-remote-executive-talent/">Why Nairobi Is the Best Source of Remote Executive Talent</a>.</p>

      <h2 style="margin-top: var(--space-7);">Engagement Formats</h2>
      <ol style="color: var(--ink-muted); padding-left: var(--space-5);">
        <li><strong>System build (project):</strong> 4–8 weeks. One defined system (SLA framework, CRM dashboard, onboarding playbook) designed, built, documented, and handed over.</li>
        <li><strong>Fractional ops manager (retainer):</strong> 10–25 hrs/week. I run the operating rhythm, own the dashboards, and continuously tighten the systems.</li>
        <li><strong>Scale-up support:</strong> Team onboarding waves, market entry operations, transition management, like the service-transition engagement Insight BPO's CEO described as "remarkably smooth."</li>
      </ol>
      <p>If your need is broader than operations (calendar, board prep, stakeholder coordination), look at the <a href="/operations-partner/">fractional operations partner</a> or <a href="/chief-of-staff-kenya/">chief of staff</a> engagements instead. Not sure which? <a href="/blog/executive-assistant-vs-chief-of-staff-vs-operations-manager/">This comparison guide</a> sorts it out.</p>

      <h2 style="margin-top: var(--space-7);">How to Start</h2>
      <p><a href="/booking/">Book a free 30-minute consultation</a>. Bring your messiest operational pain point. You'll leave with a diagnosis and a 30-day plan, whether or not we work together.</p>
